## API Summary

```javascript
// Main function
parseCSV(input, options?) → CSVResult

// CSVResult properties
result.rows              // Array of objects
result.headers           // Array of strings
result.errors            // Array of {row, message}

// CSVResult methods
result.filter(fn)        // Returns filtered array
result.sum(column)       // Returns number
result.average(column)   // Returns number
result.count()           // Returns number
result.groupBy(column)   // Returns Map
```

## Tips & Tricks

### Chaining Operations
```javascript
// Filter then sum
const engineerSalaries = result.sum(
  result.filter(e => e.dept === 'Engineering')
);
// Note: filter returns array, not CSVResult
// So you'd need to do this differently:

const engineers = result.filter(e => e.dept === 'Engineering');
const totalSalary = engineers.reduce((s, e) => s + e.salary, 0);
```

### Working with Grouped Data
```javascript
const grouped = result.groupBy('region');

// Iterate groups
for (const [region, sales] of grouped) {
  const total = sales.reduce((s, r) => s + r.amount, 0);
  console.log(`${region}: $${total}`);
}

// Get specific group
const northSales = grouped.get('North');
```

### Complex Analysis
```javascript
const data = parseCSV(csv);

// Count with condition
const count = data.filter(row => row.status === 'active').length;

// Multiple groupings
const primary = data.groupBy('category');
primary.forEach((rows, category) => {
  const secondary = rows.reduce((acc, row) => {
    if (!acc[row.subcategory]) acc[row.subcategory] = [];
    acc[row.subcategory].push(row);
    return acc;
  }, {});
  console.log(`${category}:`, secondary);
});
```

